  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Although laparoscopic gastrectomy (LG) is widely used for the treatment of early gastric
      cancer, there have been few reports of the efficacy of LAG in the management of advanced
      gastric cancer(AGC). The aim of this study is to evaluate the surgical outcomes and oncologic
      safety of laparoscopic gastrectomy for AGC.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Prospective phase II clinical trial to evaluate technical and oncological safety of LG for
      AGC

      LG procedure for AGC:

      D2 lymphadenectomy Total omentectomy for tumor with serosa exposure under laparoscopic
      exploration

      Primary end point: 3 year disease free survival secondary end point: postoperative outcomes,
      morbidity and mortality, 3,5 and 7 year overall survival, Quality of life, recurrence pattern

      Study duration: 7 years(enrollment: 4year, follow-up: 3year)
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
